<p>was for we always regarded that little bit of soil as our own.<br/>All the graves were being done up &amp; new crosses put up with the particulars of the fallen ones.<br/>A word as to the way in which the Gift stuff is distrubited I reckon it is scandalous the way the infantry get treated in regard to it  By the time the units such as A.M.C. A.S.C. &amp; artillery get their cut out of it there is not much left for the working &amp; fighting part of the Army, the very men who need it most, while the fellows who live in comparative safety &amp; comfort, get the pick of the articles, you ought to have seen</p>
